{
  "stem": "7506.1",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My name is Maurice Raynor, which is spelled M-A-U-R-I-CE R-A-Y-N-O-R.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My birth name is Maurice Rabbie.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my last name was spelled R-A-B-B-I-E.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was born on the 15th of March, 1932, in Amsterdam, Holland.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My first recollection of Amsterdam is when I was quite small.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES] Those recollections are where I lived at that time, before the war, before the Second World War, and from then on onwards.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In around about 1935, I would say, three or four years old, [PAUSES] we lived-- my father and mother and my sister-- we lived in an apartment above an apartment where lived my father's mother and father.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In other words, my grandparents on my father's side.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We lived on a street named Nieuwe Achtergracht, in center of Amsterdam.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it's a street which still exists today.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it has a canal, as so many have in Holland.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Around the corner of that street [PAUSES] was obviously another street, and it was called the Lepelstraat, which is spelled L-E-P-E-L Street.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And there lived my father's sister, only sister, known as Auntie Jet, Tante Jet, which comes from the word Henrietta.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "She was married to my uncle by marriage, and his name was Emmanuel Fontaine.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They had a son, my cousin, younger than I, whose name was Siegfried, Siegfried Fontaine Rabbie.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES] Although he was younger than myself, we did play together somewhat.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Down the canal street where I lived was another aunt of mine, who was the mother of one of my father's first cousins.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES] His name was Abraham, or in Dutch, we called him Brahm Rabbie.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He was one of twins.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And he had a daughter, Phoebe Rabbie, my age.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And with her I used to play.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And at that time, of course, also my sister.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
